						               													<description>Hooray, gift edition!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Imaginarium beloved by everyone in a compact New Year's performance - this is a ready-made gift! It contains the best winter and holiday illustrations from all previous sets, but there are also new, new cards - as many as 11 pieces,&amp;#10;they can be mixed with any set except the Jubilee. If you add a few, you get a very different Imaginarium, It has all the components for an independent game. This is a simple association game that everyone likes - this is an excellent reason to save a couple of boxes for the winter holidays.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules of the game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player chooses a chip and a set of voting cards in the same color as the chip.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Definition of the first move&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You must determine who will walk first. You can use voting cards for this. All participants take their voting cards, shuffle and draw out any card at random. The first to start is the one who pulled out the card with the highest number. You can use any other mechanics to select the player starting first. For example, we play this right in chess. Then the game goes clockwise.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game progress&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All player chips are set to 1.&amp;#10;The deck with illustration cards is shuffled and each player is given 6 cards in his hands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player makes an association.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn one of the players becomes the leader. The presenter makes an association on one of his cards, tells the association out loud to the other players and puts the hidden card upside down on the table. Each player puts out one card, the most suitable for the voiced association. Then the cards are mixed and laid out in a row.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Guessing the leader&amp;rsquo;s card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The main task of the players is to guess which of the cards laid out on the table the presenter has guessed, and to vote for her. Each player selects one voting card with the desired number and puts it face down. The host does not vote or comment on the pictures posted on the table. You cannot vote for your own picture. When everyone made a decision and voted, the voting cards are turned over and points are scored.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scoring&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players move their chips on the playing field by the number of steps corresponding to the number of points won.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
